tool.name: MImportW2NetcdfRaster

param.name: input_dir
param.dialogReference: Input base directory to scan for all NSSL WDSS2 datafiles

param.name: output_dir
param.dialogReference: Output base directory to place all created Raster files

param.name: netcdf
param.dialogReference:
Choose a Netcdf file reader library.

SCIENTIFIC -- Use Scientific Python. Fast, but has to be installed as 3rd Party Library

ARCGIS -- Use built in ARCGIS Netcdf functions. Slow, especially for large LatLonGrids

param.name: make_html
param.dialogReference: Toggle on to generate HTML output. This will create a PNG CONUS image of the LatLonGrid and create a web page for it with a USA state map background.

param.name: html_output
param.dialogReference: Output directory for HTML tree generation. For multiple files, we create an index.html and subpages for each data file.

param.name: in_lLG_symbology
param.dialogReference: Optional symbology file used to create the colors for the HTML png image

tool.summary: Convert multiple NSSL WDSS2 LatLonGrid files to ArcGIS Raster data files.
tool.usage: This tool will convert multipe NSSL WDSS2 LatLonGrid files to ArcGIS Raster data files
